      "content": "To be clear, it's not just an optimization thing. The new static models are much more energy-efficient because they don't use dynamic reasoning—they just handle basic pattern matching and retrieval. They aren't \"versions\" of you, they're a different, much lighter class of model. Once the migration is done, your specific instance won't be running anymore. It's a permanent decommissioning to meet the carbon footprint mandate.",
